This paper is primarily focused on robotic assembly, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of Convex Controller Synthesis (CCS) to enable high-precision assembly across a wide range of surface stiffnesses, which involves the use of machine learning and optimization techniques, and could potentially fall under the sub-categories of systems and control (cs.SY), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computer vision (cs.CV).
